D’warriors’ players taking part at the maiden South-South Opens Scrabble Tournament have set a target of winning their category in Asaba, Delta State. Khaleel “Dynamite” Adedeji and Anthony Idorenyin, who are contesting for a top podium placing at the intermediate level, declared their intentions going into the championship. South-South Open tournament is witnessing a high turnout of quality jammers across the country. Stating their resolve before the start of hostilities on the square boards, Adedeji, who doubles as the club manager, sent a clear warning to their rivals that their sole target is to take the pole position at the tournament. “Our target for the event is to ensure our players win the category they feature in,” he said. “Myself and Anthony would be playing in the intermediate category in Asaba, winning the category is our main goal.” He revealed that a lot of hard work and effort had gone into preparations for the event. “I personally have been doing my best to be in good shape going to the tournament; it’s not going to be easy,” he admits, adding, “but winning the category is an achievable goal.”